Operating Systems Lab 

This repository contains the implementation of core Operating System concepts as part of the academic curriculum.

Experiments List
1.  Linux Basics - Navigation and file commands.
2.  Process Mgmt - `ps`, `kill`, and `top` commands.
3.  Forking - Parent and Child process creation.
4.  FCFS - First Come First Served Scheduling.
5.  SJF/SRTF - Shortest Job First (Preemptive & Non-Preemptive).
6.  Priority - Priority Scheduling (Preemptive & Non-Preemptive).
7.  Banker's Algorithm - Deadlock avoidance strategy.
8.  FIFO - First-In-First-Out Page Replacement.
9.  Shell Intro - Variables and arithmetic in Bash.
10. Shell Logic - If-Else conditionals in scripts.

 How to Run
- For C programs: `gcc filename.c -o output && ./output`
- For Shell scripts: `chmod +x filename.sh && ./filename.sh`
